                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="1. Prepare the Chicken:

Lay the chicken breasts between two sheets of plastic wrap or parchment paper. Use a meat mallet or the flat side of a heavy pan to pound the chicken to an even thickness, about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.

Season the chicken with salt and black pepper on both sides.

2. Set Up a Breading Station:

Place the flour in a shallow dish.

In another dish, beat the eggs.

Place the breadcrumbs in a third dish.

3. Bread the Chicken:

Dredge each chicken breast in the flour, shaking off any excess.

Dip the floured chicken into the beaten eggs, ensuring it is fully coated.

Coat the chicken with breadcrumbs, pressing the breadcrumbs onto the surface to adhere.

4. Fry the Chicken Schnitzel:

Heat enough vegetable oil in a large skillet to cover the bottom, about 1/4 inch deep, over medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, carefully place the breaded chicken cutlets in the skillet. Cook for 3-4 minutes per side or until the schnitzel is golden brown and cooked through.

Place the cooked schnitzel on a plate lined with paper towels to absorb any excess oil.

5. Serve:

Garnish the chicken schnitzel with chopped fresh parsley if desired.

Serve hot with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over the schnitzel.

Optionally, serve with a side of mashed potatoes, salad, or your favorite accompaniments."
